---
source: src/sphinxdocrs/tests/apidoc.rs
expression: cmd.render_help().to_string()
---
Look recursively in <MODULE_PATH> for Python modules and packages and create one reST file with automodule directives per package in the <OUTPUT_PATH>.

The <EXCLUDE_PATTERN>s can be file and/or directory patterns that will be excluded from generation.

Note: By default this script will not overwrite already created files.

Usage: sphinx-apidoc [OPTIONS] --output-dir <OUTPUT_PATH> <MODULE_PATH> [EXCLUDE_PATTERN]...

Arguments:
  <MODULE_PATH>         path to module to document
  [EXCLUDE_PATTERN]...  fnmatch-style file and/or directory patterns to exclude from generation

Options:
  -o, --output-dir <OUTPUT_PATH>      directory to place all output
  -q                                  no output on stdout, just warnings on stderr
  -d, --maxdepth <MAXDEPTH>           maximum depth of submodules to show in the TOC (default: 4) [default: 4]
  -f, --force                         overwrite existing files
  -l, --follow-links                  follow symbolic links
  -n, --dry-run                       run the script without creating files
  -e, --separate                      put documentation for each module on its own page
  -P, --private                       include "_private" modules
      --tocfile <TOCFILE>             filename of table of contents (default: modules) [default: modules]
  -T, --no-toc                        don't create a table of contents file
  -E, --no-headings                   don't create headings for the module/package packages
  -M, --module-first                  put module documentation before submodule documentation
      --implicit-namespaces           interpret module paths according to PEP-0420 implicit namespaces specification
      --automodule-options <OPTIONS>  comma-separated list of options to pass to automodule directive [default: ""]
  -s, --suffix <SUFFIX>               file suffix (default: rst) [default: rst]
      --remove-old                    remove existing files in the output directory that were not generated
  -F, --full                          generate a full project with sphinx-quickstart
  -a, --append-syspath                append module_path to sys.path, used when --full is given
  -H, --doc-project <HEADER>          project name (default: root module name)
  -A, --doc-author <AUTHOR>           project author(s), used when --full is given
  -V, --doc-version <VERSION>         project version, used when --full is given
  -R, --doc-release <RELEASE>         project release, used when --full is given
      --extensions <EXTENSIONS>       enable arbitrary extensions, used when --full is given
  -t, --templatedir <TEMPLATEDIR>     template directory for template files
      --use-python-impl               delegate to the upstream Python sphinx-apidoc
      --ext-autodoc                   enable autodoc extension, used when --full is given
      --ext-doctest                   enable doctest extension, used when --full is given
      --ext-intersphinx               enable intersphinx extension, used when --full is given
      --ext-todo                      enable todo extension, used when --full is given
      --ext-coverage                  enable coverage extension, used when --full is given
      --ext-imgmath                   enable imgmath extension, used when --full is given
      --ext-mathjax                   enable mathjax extension, used when --full is given
      --ext-ifconfig                  enable ifconfig extension, used when --full is given
      --ext-viewcode                  enable viewcode extension, used when --full is given
      --ext-githubpages               enable githubpages extension, used when --full is given
  -h, --help                          Print help
